gurmukhi: ਖਲ ਦਲ ਬਲ ਹਰਣੰ ਦੁਸਟ ਬਿਦਰਣੰ ਅਸ ਰਣ ਸਰਣੰ ਅਮਿਤ ਗਤੰ ||
transliteration: Khal Dal Bal Haranan Doust Bidaranan As Ran Saranan Amit Gadan||
translation: Thou art the remover of the strength of the forces of foolish tyrants and causest fear fear amongst them; Thou art the Keeper of patroness under Thy refuge and hast Unlimited movement.

gurmukhi: ਚੰਚਲ ਚਖ ਚਾਰਣ ਮੱਛ ਬਿਡਾਰਣ ਪਾਪ ਪ੍ਹਾਰਣ ਅਮਿਤ ਮਤੰ ||
transliteration: Channdhal Chakh Chaaran Machchh Bidaaran Paap Prahaaran Amit Matan||
translation: Thy mercurial eyes even undo the movement of the fishes; Thou art the destroyer of sins and hast Unlimited intellect.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਜਾਨ ਸੁ ਬਾਹੰ ਸਾਹਨ ਸਾਹੰ ਮਹਿਮਾ ਮਾਹੰ ਸਰਬ ਮੲੀ ||
transliteration: Aajaan Su Baahan Saahan Saahan Mahimaa Maahan Sarab Maee||
translation: Thou hast long arms upto the Knees and art the king of kings, Thy Praise Pervades all likewise.

gurmukhi: ਜਲ ਥਲ ਬਨ ਰਹਿਤਾ ਬਨ ਤ੍ਰਿਨਿ ਕਹਿਤਾ ਖਲ ਦਲ ਦਹਿਤਾ ਸੁ ਨਰਿ ਸੂਹੀ ||੧੦||੩੦||
transliteration: Jal Thal Ban Rahitaa Ban Trin(i) Kahitaa Kahl Dal Dahitaa Su Nar(i) Sahee||10/30||
translation: Thou abidest in waters, on land and in forests, Thou art praised by forest and blades of grass; O Supreme Purusha! Thou art the consumer of the forces of foolish tyrants.10.30.
Thou art Most Powerful and Destroyer of the forces of the tyrants.
Thy Glory is unlimited and all the world bows before Thee.
The beautiful painting appears good-looking like the moon.
Thou art the Destroyer of sins Punisher of the forces of the tyrants.11.31.

gurmukhi: ਬੇਦ ਭੇਦ ਨਹੀਂ ਲਖੇ ਬ੍ਹਮ ਬ੍ਹਮਾ ਨਹੀਂ ਬੁੱਝੇ ||
transliteration: Bed Bhed Naheen Lakhe Brahm Brahmaa Naheen Bujjhe||
translation: The Vedas and even Brahma do not know the secret of Brahman.

gurmukhi: ਬਿਅਾਸ ਪਰਾਸੁਰ ਸੁਕ ਸਨਾਦਿ ਸਿਵ ਅੰਤੁ ਨ ਸੁੱਝੇ ||
transliteration: Bkaas Paraasur Souk Sanaadh Siv Ant(u) Na Sujjhe||
translation: Vyas, Parashar, Sukhedev, Sanak etc., and Shiva do not know His Limits.

gurmukhi: ਸਨਤ ਕੁਮਾਰ ਸਨਕਾਦਿ ਸਰਬ ਜੳੁ ਸਮਾ ਨ ਪਾਵਹਿ ||
transliteration: Sanat Koumaar Sanakaadh Sarab Jau Samaa Na Paavah(i)||
translation: Sanat Kumar, Sanak etc., all of them do not comprehend the time.

gurmukhi: ਲਖ ਲਖਮੀ ਲਖ ਬਿਸਨ ਕਿਸਨ ਕੲੀ ਨੇਤਿ ਬਤਾਵਹਿ ||
transliteration: Lakh Lakhmilakh Bisan Kisan Kainet(i) Bataavah(i)||
translation: Lakhs of Lakshmis and Vishnus and many Krishnas call Him “NETI”.
